'''Shatskiy Hill''' ({{coord|72|2|S|13|21|E|}}) is a [[hill]], 2,705 m, in the [[Dekefjellrantane Hills]] of the [[Weyprecht Mountains]], [[Queen Maud Land]]. Discovered and plotted from air photos by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938-1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]]. Mapped from air photos and surveys by [[Norwegian Antarctic Expedition]], 1956-60; remapped by [[Soviet Antarctic Expedition]], 1960-61, and named after Soviet geologist, [[N.S. Shatskiy]].
